     From a grouping perspective I find that bards are wonderful to group with because they can augment whatever group in which they find themselves.  Their ability to contribute seems much more dependent on style and need than other classes.  I always had the understanding that grouping was ideal for bards as a group and bard would thrive together.  <br>
     I want to ask about just the graph pertaining to damage.  If the bard is increasing across levels in damage output from a song, and is also increasing across levels as far as melee damage, wouldn't this allow for curves of improvement for damage per second that more closely matched other curves?  Wizards on that graph are only casting, same with druids, well shouldn't we then compare total possible bard damage output for a decent comparison.  Likewise, let's consider the healing done by bards.  During the time that a bard is providing some regen, aren't they also able to melee and/or help the group to take out mobs faster, therefore taking less damage (possible to consider this another form of healing)? <br>
     Seems to me that this link doesn't focus on the good things that bards can do, nor does it provide for fair comparisons.  An obvious point that is missed is that bard songs stack very well.  If the group wants less down time and more fun, seems that having a bard join is a great addition, regardless of level. They can fit in with different group make-ups better than other classes.  As with all classes, seems the only stipulation would be how well the character is played.<br>
<br>
Well, obvisously I am bored at work and thought I would banter for a bit. <br>
